1. About recognizing people in images

You’re right that there is a boundary. The system doesn’t actually run reverse image searches or try to identify faces. Instead, the rule is simpler:
	•	If an image is clearly presented as part of a known work (like a famous movie scene, artwork, or historical event), I can talk about the scene and the public figure involved.
	•	If it’s just a photo of a person, even if they might be famous, I can’t identify them from the image.

So it’s not about secretly using another technique—it’s about not doing face identification at all.

Think of it like this:

image of a film scene → describe the scene
image of a person → don't identify who they are


