4. “Dreaming while awake”

That line touches on something psychologists and artists talk about often.

The ability to imagine possibilities that don’t yet exist—daydreaming, creative vision, speculation—can lead to:
	•	art
	•	scientific breakthroughs
	•	inventions

But if imagination completely detaches from reality, it can become destabilizing.

So creativity often lives at the boundary:

imagination
↔
reality testing

Many famous thinkers—scientists, writers, inventors—spent time in that in-between space.

